FT  17 SEP 92 / Sellafield work halts after leak
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SEEPAGE of six gallons of plutonium nitrate is expected to halt
reprocessing at British Nuclear Fuels' Sellafield plant in west Cumbria for
a further four weeks, the company said yesterday, Chris Tighe writes.
No radioactivity escaped into working areas or the environment, the company
said.
BNFL, which stopped reprocessing last week after the seepage from a
plutonium evaporator was discovered, is preparing a report, which will
require Nuclear Installations Inspectorate approval, on plans to recover the
liquid.
The company said no employees would be laid off. It still hoped to catch up
on its reprocessing programme, which is its core business.
