FT  16 SEP 92 / B&amp;Q criticised on price claim
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
B&amp;Q, the DIY chain, has been reprimanded by the Advertising Standards
Authority about price claims after complaints from a village shop which said
its prices were lower.
B&amp;Q's spring 1992 catalogue said it used its buying power to make bulk
purchases and pass savings on to customers with lower prices. The ASA ruled
that: 'While a price promise was a useful protection to customers, it did
not necessarily mean that the claim to offer lower prices through
bulk-buying power was accurate.'
