<TEXT>
REPSOL, the Spanish state-owned oil, gas and chemicals group, is to delay a
placing of some 10 per cent of its equity until next year to allow
parliament to lift legal barriers to the deal.
The delay caused some surprise on the domestic markets where the placement,
which will include an international tranche and would raise some Pta60bn
(Dollars 625m), had been eagerly awaited.
The markets had understood that parliament would remove the mandatory
majority state ownership of Repsol.
A draft bill was approved last July. But Repsol said yesterday the
legislation would not be approved until December, delaying the placement
until the first half of 1993.
